<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Horror" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Horror,</orth> 1) a shuddering terror mixed with detestation: <cit><quote>a dying h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 2.3.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 3, 42</bibl></cit> (== horror of death). <cit><quote>take her hence in h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 5.441.42" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 441</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.268" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 268</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.142" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 142</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.98" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 98</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.14.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 14, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 31</bibl>.<lb />2) that which causes shuddering: <cit><quote>outface the brow of bragging h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 1, 50</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>take the present h. from the time,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 2.1.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 1, 59</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.3.69" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 69</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.3.69" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 69</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mac 5.5.13" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.1.84" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 1, 84</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.192" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 192</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.264" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 264</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.370" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 370</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 63</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>